  • Method Details

    • locationData

      LocationData locationData()
      A LocationData object stores values that are used to compute spatial coordinates. eg to access the coordinates on Locatable A, type A.locationData().coordinates();
      Returns:
      the LocationData object for this Locatable

    • mobile

      boolean mobile()
      Returns:
      true if the Locatable can change spatial coordinates over time, false otherwise

      default LocationData nextLocationData()
